strings.Value: "You have ten heartbeats to disappear. Go!"
[Attack] "I've been looking for you. Die, bandits!"
"How did you fools manage to lose the horses? We supposed to carry these boxes ourselves? What even are these iron things, and why the Hells do we need them?"

"These 'iron things' will get us rich, blockhead! It's an alchemical transmutator — I've seen them in {g|Ustalav}Ustalav{/g}. We just assemble it, turn it on, and it turns rocks into gold all on its own! Don't just stand there — get in the harness!"
"You're sure about this, then? All right, let's see if we can even get this wagon to move..."
"Look, it's that scumbag who took down the Stag Lord! And no army to be seen!"
"This shipment belongs to the baron{mf||ess}?! What did you get us into, you idiot?!"
"Lucky day! Get {mf|him|her}, everyone! If we take out the baron{mf||ess}, we can be barons ourselves!"
"That's them!" {n}Linzi whispers, pointing at the bandits.{/n} "Caught red-handed! We'll show them what happens when you take someone else's things without — ahem, we'll teach them a lesson!"
{n}Jubilost opens his mouth, about to say something, but instead just covers his face with his palm and shakes his head sadly.{/n}
"Ha, that's a laugh! Come on, try it! Let's see how you do!"
